Outputs a dataset or value to a workunit result.
```ecl
OUTPUT(myDataset);
OUTPUT(myDataset, NAMED('Results'));
OUTPUT(myDataset,, CSV);
```

Sorts a dataset by the specified fields. Prefix with `-` for descending.
```ecl
sorted := SORT(people, lastname, firstname);
sorted_desc := SORT(people, -age);
```

Removes duplicate records based on the specified fields.
```ecl
unique := DEDUP(sorted_ds, lastname, firstname);
unique_all := DEDUP(myds, ALL);
```

Creates a new table with aggregation (cross-tab report).
```ecl
stats := TABLE(people, {age, cnt := COUNT(GROUP)}, age);
summary := TABLE(sales, {region, total := SUM(GROUP, amount)}, region);
```

Defines a record layout (structure).
```ecl
PersonRec := RECORD
  STRING20 firstname;
  STRING20 lastname;
  UNSIGNED4 age;
  REAL8 salary;
END;
```

Creates a set from a single field of a dataset.
```ecl
names := SET(people, firstname);
ids := SET(filtered, id);
```

Defines a record transformation function.
```ecl
OutputRec xform(InputRec L) := TRANSFORM
  SELF.name := L.firstname + ' ' + L.lastname;
  SELF.age := L.age;
  SELF := L;
END;
```

Applies a transform to each record in a dataset.
```ecl
result := PROJECT(input, myTransform(LEFT));
result := PROJECT(input, TRANSFORM(OutRec, SELF.name := LEFT.fname, SELF := LEFT));
```

Returns the number of records in a dataset or group.
```ecl
n := COUNT(myDataset);
OUTPUT(COUNT(filtered));
TABLE(ds, {key, cnt := COUNT(GROUP)}, key);
```

Returns the sum of a numeric field across a dataset or group.
```ecl
total := SUM(orders, amount);
TABLE(orders, {region, total := SUM(GROUP, amount)}, region);
```

Returns the maximum value of a field across a dataset or group.
```ecl
highest := MAX(people, age);
TABLE(ds, {dept, maxSalary := MAX(GROUP, salary)}, dept);
```
